        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "DEFINITION: The date and time that something ends."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "NOTE: This property is neutral along two dimensions: precision (e.g., day, second, millisecond) and actual vs. planned. As such, it will generally not be asserted directly except in special cases (e.g., for time intervals)."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "NOTE: Values of predicates with different precisions can be compared since they are all formally xsd:datetimes."
